      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark problems relevant to rotating turbomachinery at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Fluent verified against Taylor-Couette flow and rotating cavity benchmarks from the ASME V&V 20 committee dataset. Discretization schemes (second-order upwind, SIMPLE pressure-velocity coupling) confirmed to reproduce analytical solutions within 0.5% for laminar cases and within 4% for turbulent cases. Code verification requirements for MRL 2 are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI below 5% for hemolysis-relevant quantities on production mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study (4.2 M, 9.8 M, 22.1 M cells) yields GCI of 2.1% for volume-averaged shear stress on the fine mesh. Wall y+ maintained between 30 and 100 for k-omega SST wall functions on all boundary surfaces. Discretization error is bounded and acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions for validation testing match CFD boundary conditions within stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump bench tests performed at 37°C blood analogue (water-glycerol 36% by mass). Inlet velocity profiles measured by PIV and applied as CFD inlet boundary conditions. Rotational speed controlled to ±2 RPM. Flow rates measured by Coriolis meter (±0.5%). Boundary condition fidelity is confirmed for all five operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH within ±20% of measured NIH across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD NIH predictions compared against three independent laboratory measurements. Maximum deviation 14.3%, mean deviation 8.7%. All predictions fall within the ±18% combined experimental uncertainty band. RH < 1 satisfied at all five operating conditions. Quantitative agreement supports use of the model for worst-case identification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validated QoI (NIH, shear stress integral) directly supports the COU decision metric (RH index).",
      "rationale": "The primary COU decision metric is the relative hemolysis index RH derived from the normalized index of hemolysis. CFD outputs the shear-stress exposure integral from which NIH and RH are computed using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. The validated quantity (NIH) is directly the COU decision quantity. Relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the operating envelope defined by the COU (5 flow-speed combinations, CPB flow range 3–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM).",
      "rationale": "Validation dataset spans flow rates 3.0, 4.0, 5.0, 5.5, and 6.0 L/min at rotational speeds 2400, 3000, and 3600 RPM, fully bracketing the COU operating envelope. Device geometry is the FDA reference pump used in the COU. Fluid properties match CPB blood analogue. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
