      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 beyond code verification already performed.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization and code verification is not separately required at MRL 2. Iterative convergence monitored to residual drop of 10^-5 for all equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%. Accepted as residual risk within MRL 2 scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not separately required at MRL 2; addressed through SQA and documented simulation workflow.",
      "rationale": "Use error controls addressed through institutional CFD simulation standard operating procedure and peer review of case setup. Separate formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2. Accepted as residual risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not separately required at MRL 2; model form uncertainty partially captured by validation comparison.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on literature evidence for rotating blood pump flows. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model is the COU-standard power-law formulation. Model form uncertainty is implicitly bounded by the output comparison results. Separate model form assessment not required at MRL 2."
